prospects.name: Start of your Strength Plan
prospects.description:
For any questions about your strength program check out [this helpful article](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4406401932050).

​

Looking for the experience of other users? Head over to our [**forum**](https://wahoox.forum.wahoofitness.com/) to see what others have to say, and/or leave your own thoughts.

​

prospects.name: Full Body 15
prospects.description:
_Want a strength training routine that covers all the bases? Our Full Body Strength series is exactly what you’re after, offering a well-rounded series of exercises that covers the lower body, core, posterior chain, and upper body. With a substantial progression, there’s enough here to keep you busy -- and improving -- for a very long time._

​

Since you've been following the proper progression up to this point, we can really start to push you to your limits and beyond. Full Body 15 throws multiple Compound Sets at you, most of which are 30 seconds or longer. Focus on maintaining great form across all the back-to-back variations. Given the increased difficulty, it is vital that you’ve mastered earlier sessions before moving on.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you?  [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Standing Hip Drive with Hands Up
- Standing Hip Drive with Hands Side to Side
- Hip Bridge with Reps
- High Plank with Foot to Hand + Opposite Rotation
- Bent Leg Tip at the Hip
- Fast Lateral Lunges with Knees Up
- Forward Lunge with Shoulder Press
- Backward Lunge with Shoulder Press
- Hip Hinge with Opposite Reach
- Hip Hinge with Shoulder Press
- Hip Hinge with Row
- Lateral Lunge with Same Hand + Shoulder Press
- Around the Clock Lunges with Same Hand
- Single-Leg Squat with Reach + Shoulder Press
- Single-Leg Squat with Opposite Reach
- Goblet Squat with Split Stance
- Squat with Wide Stance
- Hip Bridge with Hands in Air
- Hip Bridge with Hands in Air + Reps
- Frog Crunch
- Full Twists
- High Plank with Twist
- High Plank with Knee to Opposite Elbow
- Push-Up with Narrow Hands
- Push-Up with Wide Hands
- Back Extension with Arm Arcs
- Quadruped with Leg Lifts
- Quadruped with Arm Raise
- Quadruped with Arm Raise + Leg Lifts
- Side Plank with Underneath Reach
- High Side Plank with Reps + Leg Raise
- High Side Plank

prospects.name: Posterior Chain Focus 04
prospects.description:
_The primary objective of the Posterior Chain Series is to activate and strengthen the muscles on the back side of your body. This includes everything from your powerful glutes, hamstrings, and calves to the postural muscles of your upper back and neck._

​

In this routine, you’re going to keep building on the moves that you’ve mastered in the previous sessions (you have mastered them, right?). It’s time to increase the external load, though, so you’ll need a band to redirect tension and build more eccentric loading into the movements. The longer sets and difficult combinations will be challenging - embrace it! Also, even though the focus is Posterior Chain you will find integrated core moves throughout the session. Let’s rock!

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you?  [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Split Stance Side Bend w/ Arms Overhead
- Recoil Hamstring Stretch
- Tip Toe Walk
- Hip Hinges w/ Resistance Band
- Back Extension with Scapular Retraction
- High Plank w/ Opposite arm & leg raise
- Low Plank w/ Cervical Extension (Turtle)
- Low plank Chin Tucks
- Kneeling Hip Extension
- Single-Leg Hip Bridge
- Tempo Single-Leg RDL
- Tempo Hip Hinge
- 90° Reverse Fly w/ Reps
- 45° Reverse Fly w/ Reps
- Overhead Reverse Fly Reps
- Split Squats
- Split Stance Hip Hinge w/ Band
- Hip Bridge w/ Knee Squeeze
- Single-Leg Hip Bridge w/ Rotation
- Back Extensions with Arms Overhead
- Downward Dog
- Toe Touch

prospects.name: Lower Body Focus 02
prospects.description:
_Want to develop more lower body stability, strength, and power? This series takes you through a progression of exercises focused directly on your legs and hips. To mix things up a bit, we’ll occasionally throw in a few upper body, core, and mobility moves to give those legs a break._

​

We’re stepping things up a bit here with more multi-directional movement and controlled-landing jumps. These diverse movement patterns, which include deceleration, are crucial in sports like cyclocross and mountain biking, as well as in trail running and open water swimming, where you have to be reactive to a dynamic environment.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you?  [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Around the clock Heel & Toe Taps
- Recovery
- Recoil Hamstring Stretch
- Tip Toe Walk
- Single leg Hip Hinge
- Bulgarian Lunge
- Deep Squat w/Arms Crossed
- Step Overs
- Alternating-Step Under
- Split Squats
- Fast Side Lunge w/ Knee Lift
- Single leg squat to press w/ Same Arm
- Side Lunge to Knee Lift w/ Hold
- Scissor Jumps
- Back Extension with Hold
- Hamstring Hip Bridge
- Runners Stretch-Alternating

prospects.name: Core Focus 04
prospects.description:
_Looking to improve ALL of the muscles that make up your core? You’ve come to the right place. The Core Focus series builds up everything from your hip to your shoulders - front, back, and side._

​

We’re getting more complicated now, and this session includes rotational movements which demand power and control against an external load. The combination and order of movements will challenge your core strength and endurance while improving your ability to maintain stability and control when tired.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you?  [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Split Stance Backbend w/ Arms Overhead + Hold
- Quadruped T-Spine Rotation
- High Plank w/ Opposite arm & leg raise
- High Side Plank w/ toe taps
- Back Extension w/ Opposite arm & leg raise
- V ups
- Oblique Leg Lifts
- Back Extensions with Arms Overhead
- High Plank w/ Rotation & Hip Abduction
- Single-Leg Hip Bridge w/ Rotation
- Tempo Push Up Wide
- Side to Side Bear Crawls
- Pushup w/ Rotation
- Kneeling Wood Chop with Band
- Single-Leg Hip Rotations
- Sit Throughs
- KickBacks from Toes
- Reverse Wood Chop with Band
- Low Side Plank w/abduction and hold
- High Side Plank w/ bottom knee lift
- Bird Dogs

prospects.name: Full Body 01
prospects.description:
_Want a strength training routine that covers all the bases? Our Full Body Strength series is exactly what you’re after, offering a well-rounded series of exercises that covers the lower body, core, posterior chain, and upper body. With a substantial progression, there’s enough here to keep you busy -- and improving -- for a very long time._

​

This is the first routine in the Full Body series. It introduces the most basic versions of moves that make up the majority of this program. Some of these moves may seem very basic but we encourage you to focus on perfect form and execution during these early levels so that when we turn up the heat you have things nailed. As you'll see, all the exercises at the lower levels will progress in a similar fashion going forward. We're building strength, but also fine-tuning your nervous system. As the program progresses you'll be asked to complete more difficult variations on each foundational move.

​

As with all the strength training routines, it helps if you’ve done a warm-up before getting started. That can be one of your favorite yoga routines, riding your bike on the trainer for 5-10 minutes, or doing a personal stretching routine.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you? [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Kneeling Hip Drive - Hands Over Head
- Kneeling Hip Drive - Hands Side to Side
- Hip Bridge with Reps
- Bent Leg Tip at the Hip
- Goblet Squat
- Single-Leg Squat
- Backward Lunge
- Hip Hinge with Reach
- Hip Bridge with Reps
- Push-Up on Knees
- Back Extension
- Quadruped with Leg Lifts
- Plank with Leg Lifts

prospects.name: Full Body 16
prospects.description:
_Want a strength training routine that covers all the bases? Our Full Body Strength series is exactly what you’re after, offering a well-rounded series of exercises that covers the lower body, core, posterior chain, and upper body. With a substantial progression, there’s enough here to keep you busy -- and improving -- for a very long time._

​

By this point, you’re no longer struggling with single-leg balance and stability, which allows us to really focus on building raw muscular endurance in your lower body. Additionally, this routine will place greater demands on your upper body and core than any previous session has. Not only do you have 10+ minutes dedicated to the muscles above your hips, but the progression of High Planks and High Side Planks means that even the “core-work” moves have a difficult upper-body component. We’re also going to ask a lot of your movement stabilization muscles -- it’s about time they were held to account.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you?  [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

prospects.name: Full Body 17
prospects.description:
_Want a strength training routine that covers all the bases? Our Full Body Strength series is exactly what you’re after, offering a well-rounded series of exercises that covers the lower body, core, posterior chain, and upper body. With a substantial progression, there’s enough here to keep you busy -- and improving -- for a very long time._

​

By the time you arrive here, your form on the foundational exercises should be perfected to the point that even the most difficult variations don't phase you. So, to ensure you’re still challenged for continued improvements, you complete more sets of longer duration than ever before. Despite the increased time, we've kept the recovery period to 10 seconds, placing a solid demand on your cardiovascular system. No worries - thanks to your experience with the foundational moves, you'll be able to handle the extra fatigue while maintaining perfect form.

Despite the increased time, we've kept the recovery period to 10 seconds, placing a solid demand on your cardiovascular system. No worries - thanks to your experience with the foundational moves, you'll be able to handle the extra fatigue while maintaining perfect form.

The highest level in the series, this session challenges your core with more dynamic and rotational movements than any other level. The combination of challenging movements and increased set time demands full engagement - physically and mentally.

prospects.name: Lower Body Focus 04
prospects.description:
_Want to develop more lower body stability, strength, and power? This series takes you through a progression of exercises focused directly on your legs and hips. To mix things up a bit, we’ll occasionally throw in a few upper body, core, and mobility moves to give those legs a break._

​

We want to develop the power required for sprinting and surges. So it’s about time we truly challenge your strength endurance with some explosive movements followed by combinations of multi-directional exercises - and we’ll make the recoveries short. You’ll have to stay focused to keep your movements clean. We’ll mix in a few core and upper body moves to give your legs a break only to come back and hit them again. We know you’re up for the challenge so, let’s do it!

_The primary objective of the Posterior Chain Series is to activate and strengthen the muscles on the back side of your body. This includes everything from your powerful glutes, hamstrings, and calves to the postural muscles of your upper back and neck._

​

You’ve made it - the highest level in the Posterior Chain series. Here, we continue to load the back side of the body but also add in movements that require integration with other areas. Your muscular endurance will be challenged with external loads from bands, longer sets, and combination movements. To top it off, we even challenge your nervous system with tempo changes and unilateral exercises that require mental focus and muscular control.

_Want a strength training routine that covers all the bases? Our Full Body Strength series is exactly what you’re after, offering a well-rounded series of exercises that covers the lower body, core, posterior chain, and upper body. In this session, we introduce you to a few more foundational moves. Learn them well as you’ll see them throughout the program as you progress. And as you progress, we'll continue to add more difficult variations on these basics - so develop good habits now for easy mastery down the road.

prospects.name: Recovery Session A
prospects.description:
These recovery sessions are easy enough that you get the rest you need, but work you hard enough that your body continues to adapt to the new demands you place on it. You might see these sessions as too short and too easy to be beneficial, but just like a proper recovery spin, active recovery is infinitely better than doing nothing at all. Given how short this session is, we strongly recommend also doing a Yoga Session in the app first. Something like Mobilize and Activate, Balance and Agility, or Full Body Mobilization.

​
